review_blob: Cask Wibbis Down, by far the best of the 4. Black with off white head. initial sweet taste, dark fruits, mollasses. followed by eathy hop character. very well made stout
Cask, Wibbis Down. Black with off white head, sweeter than the other 3, lovely cream like feel to this beer. very well balanced. Good hop character. very nice stout.
Cask Wibbis Down. Black with white head. Tatses like a normal stout but then cherry comes through on the end. Nice sweet edge. Not a huge aroma but very pleasent.
Cask Wibbis Down, Black with white head. Initial vanilla with slight bourbon, smooth and creamy leading to more vanilla. nice bitterness level for this style. pretty nice stout overall

Cask @ WWebb in Twickenham. Amber/ornage colour, white head. tastes of orange peel, caramel. good body. Good hop and nice finish. Not quite the in your face IPAs of the East Side of London but a good solid number
Cask @ Egham beer festival. Very hoppy APA with good condition. Clear straw colour with white head. Citrus, lemon, lime flavours. Good body with a touch of sweetness. I had 2
Cask @ Watermans - Pours amber clear. White head. grassy floral aroma, light easy drinking bitter. slightly more bitter than the average 3.8%, very drinkable though.

Cask @ Queens head Feb 15th. Very black, thick creamy head. Laced well. Coffee, liquorice hints of melon. Hops at the front. Earthy, spicy, very old school English hopped. Rather nice pint. Refreshing change for a black IPA. Bottoms up Twickenham
Copper/Reddish colour, tight head. Earthy and spicey. Pretty decent session bitter. Slight toffee and caramel notes. One to try again
Cask @ Sussex - Gold in colour, slight hazy with hints of apple. Fairly drinkable golden ale.
Cask - Berrylands, Fairly standard bitter. Nothing wrong with it at all. Perfectly drinkable, nice bitterness. all in all a fair sessionable beer
Keg at brewery bar. - Cloudy blonde, very citrusy and quite enjoyable 2/3 of a pint
Cask @ Victoria - Cloudy (Though possible the bar not the brewery) fairly sweet but nice best bitter. Decent bitterness. Hopefully next time better condition.

Cask @ William Webb Twickers - Deep red with think creamy white head. Initial fruits, caremal, dark fruits. Clean bitterness that lingers through to a crisp finish. Very nice Autumn beer with a decent body to it. Seems to be the replacement for Autumn Blaze

Cask - Cricketers Richmond. Very hoppy US brown ale. Dark brown with thick white head. Hints of grapefruit. Very moorish bitterness. Aromas of lemons and oranges. Very addictive and pleasant beer. Bowled over and a convert to Twickenham ales.
Cask White Horse SW6 Appearance gold, white head. Aromas of lemon, citrus, fresh grass. Fairly bitter. slight caramel notes. Solid beer.
Cask White Horse SW6, Appearance is black with little/no head. Lots of roasted flavours. Pine needle aroma. Quite thin but overall pretty decent beer. Easily quaffable at 5.5%
beer_name: Late Knights Hairy Dog Black IPA

review_blob: Cask at White Horse SW6. Appearance pale/gold white head. Fresh smelling floral aroma. Full body with a slightly sweet initial taste that rolls into a lovely bitterness. Good expample of an English pale ale.
Tried at the White Horse SW6 - Appearance golden which good white head. Tastes of citrus, fairly sharp and dry which a long bitter finish. Overal a pretty decent golden ale
